Finally after checking all the compression algorithm I found out the problem in Android Chrome 77.

In our algorithm, after loading image from file, we use canvas.getContext(&#39;2d&#39;).drawImage to draw image into the canvas. Then for resizing the picture we use the  drawImage() on canvas to have new canvas and hear is the chrome broke the algorithm.
The brief answer is canvas.getContext(&#39;2d&#39;).drawImage function works with image as input correctly bu not with a canvas as input.

To solve the problem we first calculate the correct width and height and the read the image with the desired dimensions.

works:

        var canvas = document.createElement(&#39;canvas&#39;);
        canvas.width = img.width/2;
        canvas.height = img.height/2;
        var ctx = canvas.getContext(&#39;2d&#39;);
        ctx.drawImage(img, 0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);  

and doesn&#39;t work:

        var canvas = document.createElement(&#39;canvas&#39;);
